quantum

Class QuantumRegister

  • java.lang.Object
    • quantum.QuantumRegister

  • public class QuantumRegister
extends java.lang.Object
    The QuantumRegister represents a set of Qubits that can be operated on as a group.

      • QuantumRegister

        public QuantumRegister(int length)
        Creates a new register with the |0⟩⊗n basis state

      • QuantumRegister

        public QuantumRegister(int value,
                       int length)
        Creates a new register of a given basis state and length. If the given value has bits beyond which the length can include, they will be truncated.
        Parameters:
        value - basis state value to be stored in the bits of the register
        length - amount of qubits to be in the register

    • Method Detail

      • measure

        public int measure()
        Performs a measurement on all of the qubits in this register. This collapses their states into a basis.
        Returns:
        the state that the register collapses into

      • sample

        public int sample()
        Randomly chooses a state based on the their respective probabilities. This is the equivalent of performing a measurement, but without the collapse to a basis state, allowing for the repeated sampling of values without destroying the state.
        Returns:
        a random possible basis, weighted according to the state

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Creates a String representation of this QuantumRegister including all possible states and their respective probabilities. These probabilities will add to one, and will be separated by lines.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        a String of the probabilities of each possible basis state.

      • probabilityOf

        public double probabilityOf(int state)
        Finds the probability that when measured or sampled, this QuantumRegister will represent a given basis state. This is represented as a double value on [0,1]. The probabilities of all basis states added together will be 1. This method will only test the bits that are within the QuantumRegister, and as such it will act as a periodic function
        Parameters:
        state - the basis state to be tested for
        Returns:
        the probability of the basis state being the measured value

        Tests entanglement with a Qubit
        Parameters:
        other - the Qubit to be tested for entanglement with this QuantumRegister
        Returns:
        whether or not they are entangled, as a boolean
